quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,139,"And they say, ",1:[i.e., their milk and offspring.],2:[Of what is lawful and unlawful according to their whims.]
  6,140,"They will have lost who killed their children in foolishness without knowledge and prohibited what Allāh had provided for them, inventing untruth about Allāh. They have gone astray and were not [rightly] guided."
  6,141,"And He it is who causes gardens to grow, [both] trellised and untrellised, and palm trees and crops of different [kinds of] food and olives and pomegranates, similar and dissimilar. Eat of [each of] its fruit when it yields and give its due [zakāh] on the day of its harvest. And be not excessive.{1} Indeed, He does not like those who commit excess.",1:[In eating, as well as in all things generally.]
  7,49,"[Allāh will say], ",1:[The humble believers who are now in Paradise.  Another interpretation regards them as the people on the elevated partition.]
  7,50,"And the companions of the Fire will call to the companions of Paradise, "
  7,51,"Who took their religion as distraction and amusement and whom the worldly life deluded."
